---
title: One-Pan Sweet Chili Turkey Lettuce Wraps with Bell Pepper & Candied Peanuts
description: Our chefs came up with the perfect filling for fresh, crisp romaine leaves: Sautéed ground turkey and bell pepper simmered in a chili-soy sauce, candied peanuts for another layer of crunch, and cilantro for even more green freshness. Get ready to be wowed by the wrap.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6243286c53c79d2430519258-e9cf546c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-sweet-chili-turkey-lettuce-wraps-6243286c53c79d2430519258-10c1c2a4.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-sweet-chili-turkey-lettuce-wraps-6243286c53c79d2430519258
cuisine: Asian
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 35 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Core, deseed, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}(deseeded and finely diced). Halve, peel,
and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Trim and discard root
end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Quarter @lime{1}. Finely chop
@cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

Heat a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add
@peanuts{1/2%ounce}, @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and @water{2%tbsp}.
Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly
toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out
pan.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in pan used for peanuts over
medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and onion; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until tender and lightly browned, ~{5-8%minutes}.
Transfer veggies to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Using a #spatula{},
press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom,
~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until turkey is
cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Return veggies to pan. Stir in @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce},
and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Cook, stirring, until mixture is
thoroughly coated, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice to taste.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates; fill with turkey mixture. Garnish with
candied peanuts and cilantro. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> TIP: Alternatively, serve turkey mixture, candied peanuts, and cilantro in
> separate bowls and let everyone assemble their own wraps!